-- Athi River May Sell 50% of Its Fertilizer Division, Business Daily Reports
-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 2010-10-12T06:12:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/athi-river-may-sell-50-of-its-fertilizer-division-business-daily-reports.html
Athi River Mining Ltd.  plans to sell
as much as 50 percent of its fertilizer division, the  Business
Daily  reported, citing Managing Director  Pradeep Paunrana .  The company, which makes fertilizer, lime, sodium silicate
and cement, is in talks with a private equity group about the
sale of between 30 percent and 50 percent of the operation, the
Nairobi-based newspaper said.  Proceeds from the sale will be used to invest in its cement
operations and to build a new fertilizer plant, Business Daily
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Eric Ombok  in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net  